<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-456-878  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 456 878.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  July 24 1989 n325 p100(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Big-name users turning to aftermarket systems.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Big corporations are beginning to buy and sell their computersystems at used-computer stores.andP;  The trend towardhigher-performance workstations, systems integration and top brandnames is motivating more businesses to sell their equipment andpurchase other systems.andP;  Interstate Computer Bank, in MountainView, CA is a reseller used-equipment operation that has noticedthis trend.andP;  A few years ago, they say, Fortune 500 companieswould not buy from them.andP;  But recent market conditions have forcedthem to reassess their procurement.andP;  Management informationsystems managers have been turning from clones to brand names,since they are near in price.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Interstate Computer Bank (marketing).andO;Topic:     TrendsRetailingUsed EquipmentCompaniesPurchasing Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>